The paper deals with compressed sensing reconstruction, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of the generalized elastic net prior (GENP) is a machine learning technique, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses noise-sensitivity analysis, which is a signal processing concept (cs.SP). The simulation results involve matrix multiplication, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes a practical parameterless version of the GENP-AMP, which could fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SI).
